            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested"><name><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></name> <persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Εὐγένης" type="patronymic">Εὐγένευς</name></persName></persName> 
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p><supplied reason="lost">Un tel</supplied> fils d'Eugénès.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p><supplied reason="lost">So-and-so</supplied> son of Eugenes.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p><supplied reason="lost">Il tale</supplied> figlio di Eugenes.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>Paci thought that the tomb might be W25 Cassels. However, his description of the place, a small valley on the left side of Wadi Bil Ghadir, does not 
                correspond to such a number in Cassels' map. The side valley should be Wadi Haleg Stawat, where there is a series of tombs, numbered W62 to W97,
                amongst which this inscription might be hosted.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
